The Dallas company said in federal filings that it hopes to net about $15.4 million from the initial public offering. Internet America said it will sell 1.7 million shares, or 27% of the company, to the public for between $9 and $11 each.  Internet America encourages Web users to be squareby promoting its services with a 1-800-BE-A-GEEK sign-up number. The company offers a package that includes unlimited Web access in addition to e-mail, Internet relay chat, file transfer protocol, and news access. Other services include multiple e-mail mailboxes and personal Web sites. Its 50,000 customers (primarilyindividual users) are concentrated in North Texas. The company's Airnews.net, which is included in its dial-up access package or can be purchased separately by other customers, offers access to millions of news articles and serves about 3,800 customers in 35 countries.  UPDATE:   Internet America -- which launched a public offering in December under the ticker symbol "GEEK"-- is a public company, it must show rapid subscriber growth to please Wall Street.  The company's stock price initially shot up to more than $60 a share but has since fallen back to the $17-a-share range.

Description: Great Circle Capital is a private equity firm specializing in investments in expansion capital, buyouts, and industry consolidation.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Great Circle Capital is a private equity firm specializing in investments in expansion capital, buyouts, and industry consolidation. It seeks to invest through common equity, preferred equity, and mezzanine investment with equity participation. The firm seeks to invest in privately held or subsidiaries and divisions of larger companies with revenues in or indexed to major currencies. It seeks to invest in the global transportation sector with a focus on transportation infrastructure, shipping, transportation operating companies, energy services, logistics, freight forwarding, warehousing, and transportation assets sectors. Within transportation infrastructure, the firm seeks to invest in modernization, up gradation, and expansion of existing marine based or inland ports, terminal, and depots; facilities handling transportation of dry and liquid commodities; containerized cargos; container terminals; and also considers greenfield projects. Its investment in shipping includes companies which operate vessels in tanker, container, dry bulk, and niche shipping sectors. In the transportation operating sector, the firm seeks to invest in established air, road, and rail operators and carriers. Within the energy services sector, it prefers to invest in oil rigs, supply vessels, anchor handling tugs, standby vessels, floating production, storage and offloading vessels, heavy lift vessels, tugs and barges, and onshore supply bases and terminals servicing offshore activity. The firmâs investment in the logistics, freight forwarding, and warehousing sectors includes all other critical components of and support services to the global transportation supply chain. In the transportation assets sector, it considers investment in ships, rail wagons, containers, and related equipment. The firm seeks to invest in Russia, Southeastern Europe, Turkey, and the Baltic states although it considers all emerging markets. The firm typically invests more than $25 million per transaction in companies having cash flows more than $5 million. It considers transactions of any size with maximum equity participation of upto $30 million. The firm makes control investments and seeks strong minority positions, substantial shareholder rights, and board representation in its portfolio companies. It prefers to exit its investments between three to seven years. Great Circle Capital is based in Fairfield, Connecticut

Description: Clovi is the technology powering preventive care
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Clovi helps improve organizational performance and employee total well-being through AI-driven People Analytics. Our software as a service platform integrates with various collaboration systems (such as Email, Calendar, Slack, GitHub) to auto-ingest current and historical metadata on various forms of formal and informal employee communications. We combine this metadata with the employee profile and performance data we collect from HCM (Human Capital Management) systems, and with the data we collect from our own and third-party employee feedback surveys and wellness screenings. Our software then uses state of the art behavioral and data science techniques such as Organizational Network Analysis, Adaptive Conjoint Analysis, and Machine Learning to draw descriptive, prescriptive, and predictive insights that proactively identify at-risk or under-performing employees and suggest actionable recommendations their managers can take to mitigate the problem. Our target customers include rapidly growing or technology centric businesses with 50+ knowledge workers who communicate and collaborate electronically. We are currently working with a select group of Alpha customers to fully build out our product and prove our vision. Clovi also owns CloviFlow, a business subsidiary which sells and operates our Wellness Analytics and Data Collection software. Already producing revenue, CloviFlow has been deployed at 200+ employers to-date and has been used by their biometric screeners to screen 35,000+ employees.  Silicon Vallley based Clovi was founded by mathematicians from Harvey Mudd College and UCLA, behavioral scientist from Pitzer, and a Fortune-500 strategy consultant / serial technology entrepreneur with multiple exits.
